@node "wasmacht" "What does FixRAM?"
 
  It`s an old problem: If you`ve a CD-ROM drive with auto mount at start, your
  RAM icon appears on a other position than you`ve selected and instead of the
  RAM icon there`s the icon of the CD. This looks like @{"that" alink "sys:utilities/multiview snap"}.

  With this patch your RAM icon appears on the place where you want. Just try it!

@endnode

@node "System" "Requirements"

  An Amiga with HD and WB2.0 or higher.

@endnode

@node "Copyright" "Copyright"

 FixRAM is copyrighted by me, Andreas Falkenhahn. All rights reserved. This
 prog is cardware. If you use it, it would be nice if you send me a postcard
 from your hometown.

@endnode

@node "cardware" "How to use"

 1) Click on "Install" and follow the instructions.
 2) Start the FixRAM_prefs and select your CD-ROM driver. (should be in Sys:Storage/DosDrivers/)
 3) That was it! Reboot your computer!
 

@endnode

